<section id="menus.project">
  <title id="menus.project.title">Project</title>
  <note><para>Key shortcut description reminder: <link linkend="appendix.shortcut" endterm="shortcut.description"/></para></note>
  
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenuitem>New...</guimenuitem></term>
      <listitem>
        <para>Creates and opens a new project. See <link
        linkend="how.to.create.new.project">Create a new project</link> for
        details.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>n</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><guimenuitem>Download Team Project...</guimenuitem></term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Creates a local copy of a remote OmegaT project. See <link
        linkend="how.to.use.team.project">Use a team project</link> for
        details.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term id="menus.project.open">Open...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opens a previously created project.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>o</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Open Recent Project</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Gives access to the ten last edited projects. Clicking on one will
        save the current project, close it and open the other project.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>		
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Copy Files to Source Folder...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Copies the selected files to the <filename
        class="directory">source</filename> folder and reloads the project to
        load the new files. See <link
        linkend="project.folder.source"><guilabel>Source Files
        Folder</guilabel></link> for details.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Download MediaWiki Page...</term>

      <listitem>
		<para>Opens a dialog where you can paste the URL of the mediawiki "Edit"
		tab of the page you want to translate.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
		
        <note><para>To translate the contents of a Wikipedia page (for
        example):</para>
        <orderedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para>Click the <guilabel>Edit</guilabel> tab on the Wikipedia
            page.</para>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
            <para>Copy the URL of the page (ending with
            <guilabel>action=edit</guilabel>) and paste it into OmegaT.</para>
          </listitem>
        </orderedlist>

        <para>When you have finished your translation, to import it into
        Wikipedia:</para>
        <orderedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para>Open the <filename>.UTF8</filename> file generated in the
            <filename class="directory">target</filename> folder.</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>Copy the text and paste it into the translated version of the
            Wikipedia page.</para>
          </listitem>
        </orderedlist></note>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Reload</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Reloads the project to take external changes in source files and
        project settings into account.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>F5</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>

        <note><para>New translation memories placed in the <filename
        class="directory">tm</filename> folder while translating are loaded
        automatically as soon as the cursor moves from one segment to
        another. Similarly, the contents of the <filename
        class="directory">glossary</filename> folder are automatically
        recognized and do not require the project to be reloaded.</para></note>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Close</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Saves the translation and closes the project.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>w</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Save</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Saves the internal translation memory to the hard disk. See <link
        linkend="project.folder.omegat">omegat Folder</link> for
        details.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>s</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>		
		<para>OmegaT automatically saves translations every 3 minutes as well as
		when you close the project or quit OmegaT.</para>

        <para>The interval of 3 minutes can be changed in <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.saving.and.output"><menuchoice>
        <guimenu>Options</guimenu>

        <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>

        <guimenuitem>Saving and Output</guimenuitem>
        </menuchoice></link>.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Commit Source Files</term>

      <listitem>
        <caution><para>This function is specific to team
        projects. <emphasis>Only the team project manager should use this
        function</emphasis>. See <link linkend="how.to.use.team.project">Use a team
        project</link> for details.</para></caution>
        <para>Uploads to the repository the files that have been added or
        modified locally in the <filename class="directory">source</filename>
        folder.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Commit Target Files</term>

      <listitem>
        <caution><para>This function is specific to team
        projects. <emphasis>Only the team project manager should use this
        function</emphasis>. See <link linkend="how.to.use.team.project">Use a team
        project</link> for details.</para></caution>
        <para>Uploads to the repository the files that have been created
        locally in the <filename class="directory">target</filename> folder.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Create Translated Documents</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Creates the target documents based on your translation. The
        created target documents are located in the <filename
        class="directory">target</filename> folder. See <link
        linkend="project.folder.target"><guilabel>Target Files
        Folder</guilabel></link> for details.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>d</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>				
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Create Current Translated Document</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Creates the target document corresponding to the current document
        in translation. The created target document is located in the <filename
        class="directory">target</filename> folder. See <link
        linkend="project.folder.target"><guilabel>Target Files
        Folder</guilabel></link> for details.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>S</keycap><keycap>C</keycap><keycap>d</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>				
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Open MED Project...</term>
	  <!-- TODO add link to a format description -->
      <listitem>
        <para>Opens a project package in the MED format defined by the EU Directorate-General for Translation.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Create MED Projects...</term>
	  <!-- TODO add link to a format description -->
      <listitem>
        <para>Converts the current project into a MED package.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Properties...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Displays the <link linkend="dialogs.project.properties">Project
        properties</link> dialog to edit project languages and folder
        locations.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>e</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>		
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Project Files...</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opens the <link linkend="windows.projectfiles">Project
        files</link> window.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>l</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>				
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry id="menus.project.access.project.contents">
      <term id="menus.project.access.project.contents.title">Access Project Contents</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Gives access to the project folders. See <link
        linkend="project.folder">Project folder</link> for more details.</para>
        <para>In addition, three menu entries allow opening directly the current
        source and target documents and the writable glossary. The documents are
        opened by the application chosen by the operating system. If the
        documents do not exist yet, the options are greyed out.</para>

		<variablelist>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder">Root</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder.dictionary">Dictionaries</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder.glossary">Glossaries</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder.source">Source Files</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder.target">Target Files</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term><link linkend="project.folder.tm">TMs</link></term>
			<listitem>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term>Current Source Document</term>
			<listitem>
			  <para>The current source document is located in <link
			  linkend="project.folder.source">Source Files</link>.</para>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term>Current Target Document</term>
			<listitem>
			  <para>The current target document is located in <link
			  linkend="project.folder.target">Target Files</link>.</para>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry>
			<term>Writable Glossary</term>
			<listitem>
			  <para>The writable glossary is located in <link
			  linkend="project.folder.glossary">Glossary</link>.</para>
			  <para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		</variablelist>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Restart</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Saves the project and restarts OmegaT.  If you haven't yet saved
        the project, this manually confirms whether you really wish to
        quit.</para>
		<para><emphasis>No default key shortcut</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>Quit</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Saves the project and quits OmegaT.  If you haven't yet saved the
        project, this manually confirms whether you really wish to quit.</para>

		<para>In macOS, this menu item is listed in the Application menu.</para>
		<para>
		  <keycombo>
			<keycap>C</keycap><keycap>q</keycap>
		  </keycombo>
		</para>				
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>
